John Hasse: They met at college, Carlton College in Minnesota.

15
00:01:16.100 --> 00:01:18.099
John Hasse: Which is also my alma mater.

16
00:01:18.470 --> 00:01:21.459
John Hasse: I was born in Aberdeen, South Dakota.

17
00:01:21.750 --> 00:01:24.569
John Hasse: And when I was about 6 or 7,

18
00:01:24.960 --> 00:01:26.870
John Hasse: My fam- my father got a job.

19
00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:29.810
John Hasse: He had been teaching high school, he got a job.

20
00:01:30.120 --> 00:01:36.749
John Hasse: at the University of South Dakota, teaching math and astronomy, so we moved there, and so I became a faculty brat.

21
00:01:37.290 --> 00:01:40.319
John Hasse: And graduated high school there, and then…

22
00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:43.830
John Hasse: I left the state. I have, I had.

23
00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:49.550
John Hasse: Five siblings, my two… Oldest sisters have passed away.

24
00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:52.499
John Hasse: My brother is 92, still alive.

25
00:01:52.840 --> 00:01:55.219
John Hasse: And I have a younger sister.

26
00:01:55.450 --> 00:02:00.480
John Hasse: Margaret, who's a… A well-known poet lives in the Twin Cities of Minnesota.

27
00:02:02.630 --> 00:02:08.149
Julie Stout: What's your relationship like with your family? Are you close with your parents, or were you close with your parents? Or your siblings?

28
00:02:08.150 --> 00:02:14.170
John Hasse: I was. I was. Very close with my mother. My father was,

29
00:02:16.090 --> 00:02:19.449
John Hasse: Very smart man, and very dedicated to teaching.

30
00:02:19.650 --> 00:02:26.029
John Hasse: He could be, he had a bad temper, and that, cause some distance sometimes.

31
00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:30.160
John Hasse: But he died the week I graduated from college.

32
00:02:30.410 --> 00:02:33.559
John Hasse: He fought, cancer for 5 years and passed away.

33
00:02:33.760 --> 00:02:37.010
John Hasse: just before… days before I graduated from his.

34
00:02:37.160 --> 00:02:38.280
John Hasse: alma mater.

35
00:02:38.620 --> 00:02:43.429
John Hasse: My mother, lived 5 more years, but 3 of those were with leukemia, so…

36
00:02:43.670 --> 00:02:46.249
John Hasse: By the time I was… well, let's see…

37
00:02:48.780 --> 00:02:54.190
John Hasse: 27, I was, you could say an orphan, no parent, so… It's been…

38
00:02:54.630 --> 00:02:57.520
John Hasse: 50 years since they've been gone, and I miss them a lot.

39
00:02:59.900 --> 00:03:04.990
Julie Stout: Yeah, I definitely understand that. It's not ever easy to lose a loved one at all.

40
00:03:08.050 --> 00:03:18.710
Julie Stout: Do you have any memories that come to mind in terms of, like, fond childhood memories, or, experiences with your family, or something that just comes to mind for you?

41
00:03:19.090 --> 00:03:21.310
Julie Stout: Oh, many.

42
00:03:21.310 --> 00:03:25.570
John Hasse: Go on a long time, but, my parents were very supportive.

43
00:03:25.930 --> 00:03:29.550
John Hasse: And, we didn't have a lot of money, but they…

44
00:03:30.530 --> 00:03:34.049
John Hasse: got me piano lessons starting when I was in second grade.

45
00:03:34.540 --> 00:03:36.040
John Hasse: Turk classical piano.

46
00:03:36.320 --> 00:03:41.659
John Hasse: throughout high school and college, but by the time I was a teenager, I'd gotten interested in

47
00:03:42.230 --> 00:03:45.330
John Hasse: vernacular music, especially jazz.

48
00:03:45.450 --> 00:03:52.469
John Hasse: Started a jazz trio in high school. It's also in a rock slash soul slash blues band.

49
00:03:52.750 --> 00:03:55.570
John Hasse: As a high schooler, and…

50
00:03:57.090 --> 00:04:02.180
John Hasse: The jazz experience was very formative when I got to Carlton, I…

51
00:04:04.210 --> 00:04:07.220
John Hasse: learned everything I could about jazz, and spent a…

52
00:04:07.490 --> 00:04:11.279
John Hasse: 6 months in New York City, Studying with two top…

53
00:04:11.430 --> 00:04:14.760
John Hasse: jazz pianist, African-American jazz pianist, and…

54
00:04:14.980 --> 00:04:21.430
John Hasse: Ended up majoring in Black Studies to put my interest in black music into historical and cultural context.

55
00:04:24.200 --> 00:04:31.470
