102
00:08:40.820 --> 00:08:47.089
Julie Stout: Or something like that? Do you… did you stay in touch with any of the people that you played with in that capacity?

103
00:08:47.850 --> 00:08:50.180
Julie Stout: For some years, yes, it was called the…

104
00:08:50.450 --> 00:08:55.120
John Hasse: JB3, because… There were two Johns and a Bob.

105
00:08:55.800 --> 00:08:58.169
John Hasse: In this piano, bass, drums trio.

106
00:08:58.720 --> 00:09:06.950
John Hasse: And then I joined… Of the group of, college graduates.

107
00:09:07.570 --> 00:09:14.640
John Hasse: In a… electric band called the Five Line Transport Blues Band.

108
00:09:15.040 --> 00:09:17.620
John Hasse: And the band was doing,

109
00:09:18.100 --> 00:09:22.059
John Hasse: Well, we had to do things like Louis Luis, because the dancers wanted it.

