John Hasse: Well, the trio played, fraternity and sorority dances.

117
00:10:00.190 --> 00:10:04.260
John Hasse: nightclubs, places like that, and the…

118
00:10:04.420 --> 00:10:10.889
John Hasse: The Rock Soul Blues Bland played at, dance halls, and also fraternity dances as well.

119
00:10:11.150 --> 00:10:16.419
John Hasse: And then when I got to Carleton, I started a, a trio…

120
00:10:16.980 --> 00:10:23.139
John Hasse: piano, bass, and drums, and we called it Maiden Voyage, named after one of Herbie Hancock's…

121
00:10:23.540 --> 00:10:27.740
John Hasse: Latest, and, influential albums.

122
00:10:27.940 --> 00:10:29.010
John Hasse: Maiden voyage.

123
00:10:30.980 --> 00:10:36.690
Julie Stout: And that continued through your entire time in college, or were you able to continue it after college, or…

124
00:10:38.140 --> 00:10:40.989
John Hasse: when I graduated, it came to a close. I played for.

125
00:10:40.990 --> 00:10:41.390
Julie Stout: a while ago.

126
00:10:41.390 --> 00:10:44.769
John Hasse: in Minneapolis after that. I was in a polka band for a while.

127
00:10:44.990 --> 00:10:48.890
John Hasse: But when I came to Washington, No, wait.

128
00:10:50.550 --> 00:10:53.679
John Hasse: I'm jumping ahead. I graduate in 71.

129
00:10:55.790 --> 00:11:00.620
John Hasse: I moved to IU, Bloomington, 73.

130
00:11:01.550 --> 00:11:07.429
John Hasse: Got my master's… in… Ethnomes, ecology, and Folklore in 75.

131
00:11:08.550 --> 00:11:12.670
John Hasse: Worked on a dissertation, and… I got a research grant.

132
00:11:13.170 --> 00:11:16.510
John Hasse: And… graduated 81.

133
00:11:17.990 --> 00:11:26.419
