156
00:13:13.580 --> 00:13:16.140
John Hasse: Coming in the back door or the side door.

157
00:13:16.890 --> 00:13:22.459
John Hasse: You don't want to be that person at events. You want to be one of the people coming in the front door.

158
00:13:22.610 --> 00:13:28.430
John Hasse: And I thought, That was more becoming of a… Smithsonian curator, so…

159
00:13:28.570 --> 00:13:31.439
John Hasse: I followed that advice, and after that.

160
00:13:31.800 --> 00:13:36.179
John Hasse: If I played in public, it was part of a… Lecture concert.

161
00:13:39.130 --> 00:13:45.609
Julie Stout: that was a lot of changes in that time period! And,

162
00:13:45.700 --> 00:14:04.920
Julie Stout: just so I'm a bit more, like, clear about, like, your timeline of things, can you go over your, like, education again, in, like, the years and institutions? And then, also, if you can touch on people that inspired you, your mentors, your advisors, whoever helped you through as well, that'd be, great to hear about.

