00:21:03.460 --> 00:21:06.800
John Hasse: It was Senator George McGovern from my home state of South Dakota.

244
00:21:07.320 --> 00:21:14.970
John Hasse: Before he won the, nomination in Miami Beach, at the presidential convention.

245
00:21:15.330 --> 00:21:19.759
John Hasse: I was in charge of the whole campaign in Minnesota. Once he got the nomination.

246
00:21:20.120 --> 00:21:24.240
John Hasse: The campaign needed somebody more experienced, so they hired somebody with…

247
00:21:24.460 --> 00:21:27.099
John Hasse: was older, with more political experience, but I was in charge of it.

248
00:21:27.860 --> 00:21:31.370
John Hasse: communications, which was… campaign literature.

249
00:21:33.130 --> 00:21:36.729
John Hasse: Advertising, an organized campaign of writing letters to the editor.

250
00:21:36.960 --> 00:21:39.640
John Hasse: all that kind of stuff, and so I'd had…

251
00:21:40.250 --> 00:21:43.690
John Hasse: Various kinds of experience that you could call marketing.

252
00:21:43.800 --> 00:21:46.080
John Hasse: And so that… it seemed like a natural…

253
00:21:46.320 --> 00:21:50.130
John Hasse: If I wasn't gonna be able to… teach, and…

254
00:21:50.290 --> 00:21:53.389
John Hasse: I didn't see a future of myself as a…

255
00:21:53.870 --> 00:21:56.349
John Hasse: Full-time musician, it was just too iffy.

256
00:21:56.900 --> 00:21:59.320
John Hasse: It seemed like a… Logical.

257
00:21:59.990 --> 00:22:00.840
John Hasse: Next step.

258
00:22:01.840 --> 00:22:06.889
Julie Stout: Like, you maybe imagine there's, like, more stability there in some… in a, like, in…

259
00:22:07.510 --> 00:22:14.580
Julie Stout: In terms of, like, because teaching seemed to be more ambiguous, in terms of, like, job prospects and everything.

260
00:22:14.840 --> 00:22:18.980
John Hasse: Well, I… The fact is, I couldn't… I couldn't get a teaching job.

261
00:22:18.980 --> 00:22:19.590
Julie Stout: Right.

262
00:22:19.590 --> 00:22:20.000
John Hasse: one or two.

263
00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:20.540
Julie Stout: Yeah.

